sentence: <Builder> Mission has started.
<Builder> hello
<Architect> hello builder, we have yet another complicated structure.
<Architect> i will need a moment to look it over
<Builder> take your time.
<Builder> just give me instructions when you are ready.
<Architect> ok, we will start by using blue blocks.
<Architect> please start 1 square from the left side.
<Architect> we need to make a U shaped structure, but as if it were turned 90 degrees to the right and laying on its side
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:4 Y:1 Z:-1]

<Architect> yes
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:3 Y:3 Z:-1]
<Builder> a C?
<Architect> i made a mistake, this will actually be a rectangle.
<Architect> you have started correctly.
<Architect> we need 2 more blue blocks going horizontally and finish it off by filling in the rectangle
<Architect> 2 more on the upper and lower part, i mean
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:2 Y:1 Z:-1]
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:2 Y:3 Z:-1]
<Builder> so the orientation is correct?
<Architect> 1 more, so that it is 4 across please.
<Architect> yes this orientation is correct i believe
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:1 Y:1 Z:-1]
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:1 Y:3 Z:-1]
<Builder> like this?
<Architect> yes, now we just need to fill in that last piece to complete the blue rectangle
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:0 Y:1 Z:-1]
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:0 Y:2 Z:-1]
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:0 Y:3 Z:-1]
<Architect> actually that is a little too far.
<Architect> we just need that middle block shifted to the left and to remove the other 2 ones you just placed
<Architect> it should be a 3x4 open rectangle
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:1 Y:2 Z:-1]
[Builder picks up a blue block at X:1 Y:2 Z:-1]
[Builder picks up a blue block at X:0 Y:2 Z:-1]
<Builder> what do you mean shifted to the left?
<Architect> there should be 2 open spaces in this rectangle
<Architect> it should end on the 4th block
[Builder puts down a blue block at X:1 Y:2 Z:-1]
<Architect> yes like that
<Builder> go it
<Builder> so re move the other 2 blue blocks at the end?
<Architect> yes please
[Builder picks up a blue block at X:0 Y:1 Z:-1]
[Builder picks up a blue block at X:0 Y:3 Z:-1]
<Architect> i will refer to this shape as r-windows from here on out.
<Architect> we need to make 3 more of them in different colors.
<Architect> the tricky part is they will all be interlinked.
